OL,3,CCampaigners to appeal decision to
OL,4,Cdecline a fresh inquest into
OL,5,CSummerland fire
OL,7,FMr Wannenburgh said 'a lack of fresh
OL,8,Fevidence' meant he was unable to carry
OL,9,Fout their request, adding that the
OL,10,Ffamilies may have 'misunderstood' the
OL,11,Fverdict, explaining how the legal
OL,12,Fdefinition does not necessarily place
OL,13,Fthe blame on those who died.
OL,15,FHowever, writing to the Attorney
OL,16,FGeneral, Mr Mackin said Mr Wannenburgh
OL,17,Fhas 'misdirected himself' with the
OL,18,Fmeaning of 'misadventure', claiming
OL,19,Fthere is 'no legal basis' for his
OL,20,Freasoning around the current verdicts.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
