OL,3,CCampaigners to appeal decision to
OL,4,Cdecline a fresh inquest into
OL,5,CSummerland fire
OL,7,FHe writes: 'The intended act (lighting
OL,8,Fthe fire) was not carried out by any
OL,9,Fof the proposed applicant's deceased
OL,10,Floved ones means that no rational
OL,11,Fperson could consider that 'death by
OL,12,Fmisadventure' is a correct verdict to
OL,13,Fbe returned on the facts.'
OL,15,FHe added that 'unlawful killing'
OL,16,Fshould be considered 'based on the
OL,17,Ffacts of the Summerland fire disaster'.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
